cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a data-driven approach for deep convolutional neural network compression, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The optimization method used in the paper involves backpropagation and Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD), which are also commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on the ImageNet dataset, which is a common benchmark in multimedia (cs.MM).
